          "",
          "",
          "LAB"
        ],
        [
          "Staff Generated History"
        ],
        [
          "You hate lies. Even more than lies, you hate cover ups.  The truth must be free because how else can we live honest lives?  You were a newspaper reporter during the Golden Age of print, the 1940s to the 1960s; you took to it like a fish in water. You started as a typesetter before you were even out of highschool, but by your twenties, you were done with small town affairs (you can only write about so many church fundraisers) and went back East, to where the real action was. You were always a little scrappy and throwing a punch was easy as throwing out an insult. No one was ever going to accuse you of writing a check your ass couldn’t cash. Which is how you caught the attention of the C.K. Graham. They started as your informant, but quickly development into more of a mentor-like position. But then… they become your sire. And you knew a truth beyond any you’d known before. The Philosopher Kings of the Brujah burns in you just as bright as the Warriors who stand on the front lines. You’re going to be both and tell the tales that come from it all."
        ],
